The paper discusses a new approach to meta-learning using a memory augmented neural network, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on addressing the issue of memory interference in existing models, which suggests a focus on neural network architecture and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses image datasets (Omniglot and MNIST), which suggests a focus on computer vision, and the proposed model involves encoding label information, which suggests a focus on natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely sub-categories.
